org.orgName: District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding Terms at Seattle, for the Counties of King and Kitsap.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of C.F. Reed by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said C.F. Reed shall be called or charged, before the HON. Roger S. Greene R.A. Jones, Judge of the aforesaid Court at the Court Room thereof in Seattle on this 27th day of April 1888 at 2 o'clock P.M. to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said C.F. Reed And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. Roger S. Greene R.A. Jones, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 27th day of April A.D. 1888
